              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>A type <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is said to be <html:em><html:strong>contractible with centre <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a:A]]></fr:tex></html:strong></html:em> when every <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x:A]]></fr:tex> is equipped with an identification <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\chi _x\colon  a = x]]></fr:tex>. We say that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is <html:em><html:strong>contractible</html:strong></html:em> when it comes equipped with some <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a:A]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is contractible with centre <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a]]></fr:tex>. We sometimes refer to a contractible type as a <html:em><html:strong>singleton</html:strong></html:em>.</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
