                <fr:title text="n-truncated type"><html:span style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>-truncated</html:span> type</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
                <fr:meta name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001G.agda" type="external">erct-001G.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>Given a <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001F.xml" title="Indexing of truncation levels" addr="forest://erct/erct-001F" type="local">truncation level</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>, we define what it means for a type to be <html:em><html:strong><html:span style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>-truncated</html:span></html:strong></html:em> by induction:</html:p>
                <html:ul><html:li>a type is <html:em><html:strong><html:span style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[-2]]></fr:tex>-truncated</html:span></html:strong></html:em> when it is <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001H.xml" title="Contractible type" addr="forest://erct/erct-001H" type="local">contractible</fr:link>;</html:li>
  <html:li>a type is <html:em><html:strong><html:span style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[-1]]></fr:tex>-truncated</html:span></html:strong></html:em> when it is a <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001I.xml" title="Proposition" addr="forest://erct/erct-001I" type="local">proposition</fr:link>;</html:li>
  <html:li>for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n \geq  0]]></fr:tex>, a type <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is <html:em><html:strong><html:span style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>-truncated</html:span></html:strong></html:em> when for every <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x,y:A]]></fr:tex> the identification type <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x=y]]></fr:tex> is <html:span style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n-1]]></fr:tex>-truncated</html:span>.</html:li></html:ul>
                <html:p>So, in particular, a <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[0]]></fr:tex>-truncated type is precisely a <html:em>set</html:em>. We shall often refer to <html:span style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>-truncated</html:span> types as <html:em><html:strong><html:span style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>-types</html:span></html:strong></html:em>.</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
